The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, Aug. 7: Rating agency Icra today filed a draft red herring prospectus with the Securities and Exchange Board of India for an offer for sale of 25.81 lakh equity shares of Rs 10 each for cash at a price to be decided through the book-building process. The offer for sale is by IFCI, State Bank and administrator of the specified undertaking of Unit Trust of India. The shares constitute 25.81 per cent of the fully diluted post-offer capital of Icra.

 Mumbai, Aug. 7: Satyam Computer Services has formed an alliance with Texas-based Planview, an enterprise portfolio management software organisation. The Satyam-Planview alliance will deliver world-class IT portfolio management solutions to its customers, said G.B. Prabhat, Satyams director (consulting and enterprise solutions).

 New Delhi, Aug. 7: Malaysian mobile operator Maxis Communications Berhad, which has a majority stake in its Indian JV Aircel, has applied for mobile licences in 11 circles to be a pan-Indian player.

 New Delhi, Aug. 7: Hutchison Telecom International, the Hong-Kong based parent of Hutchison that operates the Hutch-Essar JV in India with the Essar group, has said the termination of BPL Mobile Mumbai circles merger deal by its Indian partner was wrong. 

 New Delhi, Aug. 7: Indian Oil Corporation (IOC) has signed agreements to raise foreign currency loans worth $370 million for funding its oil import requirements. 

 Mumbai, Aug. 7: McDowell amp; Company today said Bombay High Court has sanctioned the composite scheme of arrangement with Shaw Wallace Distilleries, Triumph Distillers amp; Vintners and Baramati Grape Industries.

 Mumbai, Aug. 7: iGATE Global Solutions has merged US-based subsidiary Symphoni Interactive LLC with itself.




